    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-07-07T14:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-07-07T14:13:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <head>155. Telegram 159191 From the Department of State to the Embassy in the Soviet
                        Union<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d155fn1">
                        <p>
                            <seg type="summary">Summary: The Department transmitted the “non-paper”
                                that the Soviet Embassy had delivered in reply to the démarche
                                Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for European Affairs <persName
                                    corresp="#p_AJA_1">Armitage</persName> had made to Soviet
                                Minister Counselor Vorontosov in June and provided an unofficial
                                translation of the paper.</seg>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <seg type="source">Source: National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG_1"
                                    >RG</gloss> 59, Central Foreign Policy File, D750234–1086.
                                Secret; Priority. Drafted by Zook; cleared by McNeill, <persName
                                    corresp="#p_BAC_1">Borg</persName>, Ifft, Shinn, and Palmer;
                                approved by <persName corresp="#p_AJA_1">Armitage</persName>.
                                Repeated for information to the Mission to the <gloss
                                    target="#t_IAEA_1">IAEA</gloss> at Vienna and to London.
                                Telegram 133038 is <ref target="#d148">Document 148</ref>.</seg>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1975-07-07T19:13:00+00:00">July 7, 1975, 1913Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>159191. Subject: Soviet Response on Our Venting Démarche. <gloss
                        target="#t_REFReftel_1">Ref</gloss>: State 133038. For <gloss
                        target="#t_USDel_1">USDel</gloss>—TTB/PNE Talks.</p>
                <p>1. Soviet Embassy today delivered “non-paper” to <gloss target="#t_EURSOV_1"
                        >EUR/SOV</gloss> desk officer in reply to oral démarche Deputy Assistant
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_AJA_1">Armitage</persName> made June 6 to
                        <persName corresp="#p_VY_1">Vorontsov</persName> on venting issue.</p>
                <p>2. Unofficial translation of non-paper as follows: <hi rend="italic">Begin
                        text:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The information on the question raised by the American side is already
                    transmitted to the <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> Government on March 12,
                    1975. This information contains the answer to the question which was put by the
                    American side and the Soviet side has nothing to add to it.</p>
                <p>At the same time the Soviet side underlines, that the Soviet Union attaches great
                    importance to the compliance with the provisions of the Treaty of Moscow of
                    August 5, 1963 and that appropriate Soviet authorities were and are taking
                    measures directed at strict observance of the requirements of the said treaty.
                        <hi rend="italic">End text.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_KHA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
